# screws-box code ownership.
#
# GitHub auto-requests review from the listed owner(s) for every PR that
# touches a matching path; the master ruleset can additionally require a
# code-owner approval. Patterns follow .gitignore syntax and the LAST matching
# pattern wins.
#
# The repository lives under the `egeek-tech` organization. A bare org handle
# (`@egeek-tech`) is rejected by GitHub's CODEOWNERS validator ("Unknown
# owner"), so ownership is assigned to a team. Membership is managed at
# https://github.com/orgs/egeek-tech/teams/security-manager — add members there
# rather than editing this file.

# Catch-all — owns every path in the repo.
* @egeek-tech/security-manager
